2. Standard Module Template (e.g., Masters / State)

Each module should have 4 key files:

Page Component
Example: StatePage.jsx
Handles useState, useEffect, fetch data, form submission, grid, dialogs.
Service Layer
Example: stateService.js
All API calls in one place using apiClient (axios).
Use try/catch in both Page and Service layer for robust error handling.
Schema (Validation)
Example: state.schema.js
Use Yup for form validation.
Columns / Grid Config
Example: state.columns.js
Define grid columns, formatters, actions.

✅ Optional: useCrud.js hook to reduce repetition (fetch, save, update, delete) for all modules.

3. Common Reusable Components
MasterForm.jsx → Dynamic form generator (text/select/switch + validation + submit/reset buttons)
MasterGrid.jsx → Dynamic grid (AG Grid community edition) with export CSV/Excel/PDF
LeftPanel.jsx / TreeMenu.jsx → Sidebar navigation
Navbar.jsx / LogoutButton.jsx → Top navigation
4. Redux Slice Standard
Each module does not need a slice unless you want to manage global state.
Only menuSlice.js is required for active menu tracking.
5. Naming Conventions
Components → PascalCase (StatePage.jsx, MasterForm.jsx)
Services → camelCase with module (stateService.js)
Schema → camelCase (state.schema.js)
Columns → camelCase (state.columns.js)
Redux slices → moduleSlice.js
6. Routing Standard
// App.jsx
<Routes>
  <Route path="/" element={<Home />} />
  <Route path="/masters/state" element={<StatePage />} />
  <Route path="/masters/country" element={<CountryPage />} />
  <Route path="/leave/application" element={<LeaveApplication />} />
  <Route path="/payroll/salary" element={<SalarySlip />} />
  {/* add new modules here */}
</Routes>
7. Recommended Workflow for New Module
Create folder: features/moduleName/
Add: ModulePage.jsx, moduleService.js, module.schema.js, module.columns.js
Reuse MasterForm & MasterGrid for UI
Add API endpoints in moduleService.js
Add route in App.jsx
Add menu item in LeftPanel.jsx and/or TreeMenu.jsx
8. Benefits of This Structure
Scalable: Easy to add new modules.
Consistent: Juniors can follow the same pattern.
Reusable: MasterForm & MasterGrid used across modules.
Separation of Concerns: Page, Service, Schema, Columns clearly separated.
Maintainable: Easy to debug, extend, or replace components.